subSubSection.paragraph:
ABDOMEN (
Fig. 5C
). Black to dark brown. Tergum 1 with gray pollinosity, covered with black basal sockets of pile and with short pale yellow pile; tergum 2 with pollinose posterior margin and narrow medial fascia, interrupted in the middle, covered with pale yellow pile; terga 3 and 4 with pollinose posterior margin and broad medial fasciae (
Fig. 5C
); tergum 3 covered with pale yellow pile except anterior half with few short black pile; tergum 4 covered with long golden-yellow pilosity (
Fig. 5C
). Sterna reddish-brown, covered with pale yellow pile.
